marie noe (born august 23, 1928) is an american serial killer. she was convicted in june 1999 of murdering eight of her children. between 1949 and 1968, eight of the ten noe children died of mysterious causes which were then attributed to sudden infant death syndrome. all eight children were healthy at birth and were developing normally. two other children died of natural causes. noe pleaded guilty in june 1999 to eight counts of second-degree murder, and was sentenced to 20 years' probation and psychiatric examination.